<h2 class="bold font-l">Mordred Offs Celenike</h2>
<p class="_pmvv-vidbox-descTxt">
While trying to force Astolfo to kill Sieg using her Command Spell, Celenike is unceremoniously decapitated by a disgusted Mordred. Given her actions, no one cares about her. </p>
<p class='example_row'>Example of:<br><a href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AssholeVictim" class='trope-example-link'>Asshole Victim</a></p>
</div>
<div class="video-examples-thumbs">
<a href="#video-link" data-video-id="7shvg4" data-video-descrip="When talking to Chiron, Caules reflects back in the past when his older sister used to have a pet dog. However, said dog had a demon inserted into it by their father to display the dangers of Spirit Evocation. When burying the dog, Fiore doesn't take it well at all. " data-video-title="Fiore's Dog" data-video-url="https://d1w6li7s85ibls.cloudfront.net/qvbr/7shvg4_640x360p_qvbr.mp4" data-video-thumbnail="https://static.tvtropes.org/trope_videos_transcoded/images/sd/7shvg4.jpg" data-video-trope="Main/BreakTheCutie" data-video-tropename="Break the Cutie" data-video-approval="APPROVED" data-video-troper-rating="" data-video-average-rating="" data-video-rating-count="" data-video-media-sources="LightNovel/FateApocrypha" class="video-launch-link video-overlay-link video-background-image lazy-image" data-src="https://static.tvtropes.org/trope_videos_transcoded/images/sd/7shvg4.jpg">
<p><span class="bold">Fiore's Dog</span></p>
